<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFB46A0BFD1B94FF1C00BF33" pageId="79" pageNumber="837" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB46A0BFD1B94FF1B33B9F5" blockId="79.[741,1334,560,987]" box="[743,1331,678,711]" pageId="79" pageNumber="837">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB46A0BFD1B94FF1D76B9F5" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" box="[743,886,678,711]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotomanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotomanes</taxonomicName>
is sister to la within Eptesicini.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB46A0BFD1994911B32B8E9" blockId="79.[741,1334,560,987]" pageId="79" pageNumber="837">
Form imbrensis is tentatively considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB46A0BFC4494A11A18B827" authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1851" box="[952,1048,760,789]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotomanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">ornatus</taxonomicName>
until more refined studies validate its distinctiveness. Form 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB46A0BFD1B951D1D85B857" baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[743,901,836,869]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emarginatus">emarginatus</taxonomicName>
(known only from the holotype) has been recognized as a distinct species but is generally considered a synonym of S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFB46A0BFC8595E31DD9B8E9" authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1851" box="[889,985,954,987]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotomanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="837" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">ornatus</taxonomicName>
, which is followed here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB46A0BFF7C95B91C00BF33" blockId="79.[125,1335,992,3078]" box="[128,512,992,1025]" pageId="79" pageNumber="837">‘Two subspecies recognized.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
